decks.notes: The deck aims to quickly assemble the Cephalid Breakfast combo, utilizing Nomads en-Kor, Cephalid Illusionist, and Shuko to mill the library and win the game with Thassa's Oracle or Dread Return. The deck also includes protection in the form of Force of Will and disruption with cards like Cabal Therapy. Urza's Saga is used to tutor for key combo pieces, while Tamiyo, Inquisitive Student provides card draw. The inclusion of Yorion, Sky Nomad allows for extra value and flexibility in terms of sideboarding options.

This deck focuses on using powerful artifacts, mana acceleration, and card draw to quickly overwhelm opponents and control the game. The key strategy is to ramp up mana with cards like Grim Monolith and Metalworker to quickly play out threats like Karn, the Great Creator and Blightsteel Colossus. The Urza lands and Urza's Saga provide additional mana acceleration and versatility. The deck also includes cards like Kuldotha Forgemaster to tutor for specific artifacts and disrupt opponents with cards like Kozilek's Command and Portal to Phyrexia.

The deck focuses on quickly deploying threats and disrupting the opponent's game plan through counterspells and removal spells. By pressuring the opponent early with creatures like Brazen Borrower and Murktide Regent, while also controlling the board with cards like Fatal Push and Force of Will, the deck aims to maintain tempo and dictate the pace of the game. With a mix of disruptive spells and efficient threats, the deck aims to outmaneuver the opponent and secure a victory through a combination of aggression and disruption.

This deck focuses on quickly filling the graveyard with powerful creatures like Archon of Cruelty and Atraxa, Grand Unifier, then using cards like Reanimate and Animate Dead to bring them back into play. The deck also utilizes discard spells like Thoughtseize and Unmask to disrupt the opponent's strategy while generating mana with cards like Dark Ritual and Chrome Mox. With efficient removal options in Smallpox and Liliana of the Veil, as well as land disruption from Wasteland, this deck aims to overwhelm the opponent with powerful reanimated threats.

The main idea of this Legacy Combo deck is to quickly assemble the combo pieces of Cephalid Illusionist and Nomads en-Kor to mill the entire library, triggering Narcomoeba and Thassa's Oracle to win the game on the spot. The deck also includes control elements with Force of Will and Swords to Plowshares, as well as card selection with Brainstorm and Ponder. Urza's Saga provides additional utility and card advantage, while Prismatic Ending acts as removal. The deck aims to win the game in a single explosive turn with its combo pieces.

This Control - Stoneblade deck focuses on using creatures and equipment to control the board and disrupt the opponent's game plan. With a mix of disruptive creatures like Meddling Mage and Skyclave Apparition, along with powerful equipment like Stoneforge Mystic and Kaldra Compleat, the deck aims to outvalue and outmaneuver opponents. The inclusion of Aether Vial allows for creatures to be put into play at instant speed, while cards like Recruiter of the Guard help find key pieces of the deck. The deck also includes a variety of utility lands and spells to further disrupt the opponent's strategy.

This deck focuses on quickly and efficiently comboing off using a combination of creatures and spells to mill through the library and win the game with Thassa's Oracle or Reanimate/Dread Return shenanigans. The key is to use mana acceleration like Lotus Petal and Simian Spirit Guide to power out your combo pieces quickly, while also disrupting the opponent's game plan with cards like Thoughtseize and Pact of Negation. The goal is to assemble your combo pieces and win the game before your opponent can stop you.

This Boros Aggro deck focuses on aggressive creature plays with support from powerful spells like Swords to Plowshares to control the board. The deck aims to overwhelm the opponent quickly with efficient creatures like Amped Raptor and Ocelot Pride, while utilizing cards like Containment Priest and Fable of the Mirror-Breaker to disrupt the opponent's strategy. The inclusion of Ajani, Nacatl Pariah and White Orchid Phantom adds additional power and versatility to the deck, making it a formidable threat in Legacy 1 vs 1 matches.

The main concept of this Eldrazi Aggro deck is to quickly ramp up mana using cards like Ancient Tomb and Lotus Petal, while also disrupting the opponent's game plan with cards like Thought-Knot Seer and Chalice of the Void. The deck aims to play aggressive Eldrazi creatures like Devourer of Destiny and Glaring Fleshraker to put pressure on the opponent and close out the game quickly. It also utilizes cards like Sowing Mycospawn and Territory Culler to generate additional value and maintain board presence. The goal is to overwhelm the opponent with powerful Eldrazi threats before they can stabilize.

The main concept of this deck is to utilize Mystic Forge along with various artifact cards to create a powerful combo that generates mana and card advantage. By manipulating artifacts with cards like Basalt Monolith, Voltaic Key, and Grim Monolith, the deck aims to cast powerful spells such as Emrakul, the Aeons Torn and Karn, the Great Creator. The inclusion of cards like Lotus Petal and Urza's Saga allows for ramping and searching for key pieces of the combo. The deck's ultimate goal is to overwhelm the opponent with a powerful board state and end the game quickly.

The main idea of this deck is to quickly put powerful creatures like Griselbrand, Emrakul, and Atraxa into play using cards like Show and Tell, Sneak Attack, and Omniscience. The deck has a lot of ways to protect its combo pieces, with cards like Force of Will and Flusterstorm. The deck also includes fast mana sources like Lotus Petal and Simian Spirit Guide to help ramp into its big threats. The goal is to overwhelm the opponent with powerful creatures and win the game before they can respond.

This deck aims to quickly generate mana through fast acceleration cards like Lion's Eye Diamond and Dark Ritual, to then cast a powerful combo spell like Ad Nauseam or Tendrils of Agony. The deck utilizes card draw and manipulation spells like Brainstorm and Ponder to find key combo pieces, while also disrupting the opponent's game plan with cards like Duress and Thoughtseize. It can quickly transition from setting up its combo to going off and winning the game in a single turn, making it a highly efficient and deadly storm deck in the Legacy format.
